    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Kyle Tucker** (78.73). **Gunnar Henderson** earns the top spot in our lineup, leveraging a favorable matchup against Roupp and a massive 16% park boost that keeps his projected efficiency comfortably in the elite tier. **Kyle Tucker** follows closely, benefiting from a wind-aided environment and a favorable projected spot at the top of the order, assuming his lineup placement holds. **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) is our most efficient mid-order play; he benefits significantly from a 17% boost against Sugano\u2019s projected struggles, making him a cornerstone for production today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on our roster involved **Nolan Schanuel** (47.94), who narrowly missed the starting cut. While **Nolan Schanuel** projects reasonably well, the combination of an elite arm in Burns and a 38% rain risk suppressed his ceiling enough to keep him on the bench in favor of more efficient platoon configurations. Similarly, we are exercising caution with **Miguel Vargas** (51.96) and **Josh Lowe** (51.62). **Miguel Vargas** faces a 31% rain risk, and while **Josh Lowe** benefits from favorable wind conditions, the volatility of facing an elite arm like Burns forces us to prioritize our high-floor starters like **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.23) and **Andy Pages** (62.85). We will continue to monitor the weather patterns for **Miguel Vargas** and **Josh Lowe** throughout the afternoon; should the rain risk escalate, we are prepared to pivot to bench depth like **Luis Robert Jr.**, despite his current suboptimal platoon matchup against Ginn.",
